  "notes": "Baseline improvement 9/10: elastic net regularisation combining L1 (l1_weight=1e-5) with L2 (weight_decay=1e-4). L1 alone (brca_omics_l1, CI=TBD) drives sparsity \u2014 pushing weights for uninformative genes toward exactly zero \u2014 but can be unstable when genes are correlated (many paths through correlated gene blocks are equally valid). L2 alone (weight_decay) shrinks all weights uniformly but never zeros them out. Elastic net gets sparsity from L1 while L2 stabilises the solution under correlation: when two genes are equally informative, L2 keeps both at moderate weight instead of arbitrarily zeroing one. For RNA-seq data with well-known pathway co-expression structure this combination is theoretically motivated. The L1 penalty targets the first linear layer's weights (1000\u00d7128 = 128k weights) via model.regularized_weight; L2 weight_decay acts on all parameters. All other settings identical to brca_omics_topk1000 (CI=0.6017)."
